What is a hotkey... and what requirements does the hardware need?
https://docs.bittensor.com/Installation.html
Thanks

-- Create a coldkey (wallet), and then create a hotkey assigned to that coldkey/wallet.
-- Register the hotkey on the network. This is a POW-style process that can take hours or days depending on how much compute you throw at it.
-- Keep a min of 1024 staked to the hotkey to prevent it from being de-registered. hotkeys have a 8 hour grace period after registration and after that they must have either stake, or be sufficiently proving their value to the network by serving a model that the network deems good/novel enough.
-- Run the validator script with your hotkey, using a powerful enough machine, which you can either buy or rent virtually. Not sure on current requirements for a Validator, but they are less than for a Server (ie. you don't need a GPU just yet). I think Validators earn about 1.5t/day/1000 tao staked.
